Restaurant critic and festival curator Leo Schofield claimed living in Tasmania was the unhappiest time of his life . 
  He moved to Hobart to set up a Baroque music festival but decided to relocate back to New South Wales after the Tasmanian Government cut the festivals funding by 25 per cent . 
  He said the decade he spent in the state left him bitter and depressed . 
  He described Tasmanians as 'dregs, bogans and third-generation morons' The Tourism Industry Council of Tasmania responded to his comments calling them 'blatant mistruths'